        body: "Use the <strong>present simple</strong> tense for things you do regularly — every day, every week, etc. <em>I wake up at 7. She goes to work by bus. He reads before bed.</em> The verb changes for <strong>he / she / it</strong>: add <strong>-s</strong> or <strong>-es</strong>. Rules: most verbs + <em>s</em>: <em>work → works, eat → eats.</em> Verbs ending in -ch, -sh, -ss, -x, -o + <em>es</em>: <em>watch → watches, go → goes.</em> Irregular: <em>have → has, be → is.</em>",
        bodyEs: "Usa el <strong>presente simple</strong> para cosas que haces con regularidad — cada día, cada semana, etc. <em>I wake up at 7. She goes to work by bus. He reads before bed.</em> El verbo cambia para <strong>he / she / it</strong>: añade <strong>-s</strong> o <strong>-es</strong>. Reglas: la mayoría de los verbos + <em>s</em>: <em>work → works, eat → eats.</em> Verbos terminados en -ch, -sh, -ss, -x, -o + <em>es</em>: <em>watch → watches, go → goes.</em> Irregulares: <em>have → has, be → is.</em>",
