        bodyEs: "Los adverbios de frecuencia indican CON QUÉ FRECUENCIA ocurre algo: <strong>always (siempre, 100%), usually (normalmente, ≈80%), often (a menudo, ≈60%), sometimes (a veces, ≈40%), rarely/seldom (raramente, ≈10%), never (nunca, 0%).</strong> Colócalos <strong>antes del verbo principal</strong>: <em>I always eat breakfast. She never drinks coffee. He often goes to the gym.</em> Excepción — colócalos <strong>después del verbo 'be'</strong>: <em>He is always late. She is usually happy.</em>",
