        bodyEs: "El <strong>presente perfecto</strong> = <strong>have/has + participio pasado</strong>: <em>I have finished. She has arrived.</em> Úsalo para acciones que empezaron en el pasado y continúan ahora, con <strong>for</strong> + un período y <strong>since</strong> + un punto de inicio: <em>I have lived here for ten years</em> (durante diez años). <em>She has worked there since 2020</em> (desde 2020). Aprende los participios irregulares comunes: <em>be → been, go → gone, see → seen, do → done, make → made, take → taken, eat → eaten, write → written</em>.",
